    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i feel like there’s nothing left inside. i used to see colors and shapes in everything, like the world was talking to me through the canvas. now it’s just... grey. silent. it’s like the part of me that actually lived died, and i’m just walking around in this shell of a person. it’s exhausting trying to pretend there's still a soul in here.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Feeling emotionally numb and detached from life can often lead to dissociation or burnout, sensations that hurt deeply even if the pain isn't physical. If these feelings persist or worsen, seeking support from a mental health professional or a trusted person can offer a compassionate path to healing and reclaiming those vivid experiences you remember. You are not broken beyond repair; many people have walked through similar dark enclosures and found their color again with the right encouragement and self-compassion.",
      "source": "target",
