    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it doesn't feel like burnout. burnout is when you're tired but you still know who you are. this is different. it feels like the core is just... gone. like the music stopped and the instrument is just sitting there, collecting dust. i'm just going through the motions of a person, but there's nobody home. how am i supposed to keep carrying this body around when there's nothing left in it to justify the weight?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
